
[1]locate

   LO'CATE, v.t. [L. loco,locatus.]

   1. To place; to set in a particular spot or position.

   2. To select, survey and settle the bounds of a particular tract of
   land; or to designate a portion of land by limits; as, to locate a
   tract of a hundred acres in a particular township.

   3. To designate and determine the place of; as, a committee was
   appointed to locate a church or a court house.
